#The twenty-eighth letter of the Russian [[Cyrillic]] alphabet is named '''твёрдый знак''' (tvjórdyj znak, "hard sign"). It has no sound of its own, but modifies that of the preceding consonant. It is preceded by [[Щ]] and followed by [[Ы]].

